---------------------------------------------------------------------------
APPENDIX A: END-USER COMPLIANCE AND JURISDICTIONAL ADDENDUM
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

By executing or compiling this Software (BearSentinel), you acknowledge the 
following legal distinctions regarding its deployment:

1. STRICTLY METADATA (FEDERAL COMPLIANCE)
This Software is designed solely to parse unencrypted Control Channel (C-CH) 
telemetry and metadata. It does not decrypt AES, DES, or any encrypted voice 
payloads. Any attempt to modify this codebase to intercept or decrypt secure 
communications is a violation of federal law (ECPA).

2. HARDWARE DEPLOYMENT AND MOBILE RESTRICTIONS (STATE JURISDICTION)
The legality of utilizing BearSentinel is highly dependent on your physical 
hardware deployment. Under specific state laws (such as Florida Statute 843.16), 
installing or operating active radio monitoring equipment in a motor vehicle 
is a criminal offense unless you hold a valid FCC Amateur Radio (Ham) license. 
Operating this software to facilitate or evade detection during the commission 
of a crime carries severe felony enhancements (e.g., F.S. 843.167). 

3. ABSOLUTE INDEMNIFICATION
The author(s) provide this codebase strictly for educational and diagnostic 
purposes. The author(s) have no control over your physical deployment, radio 
hardware, or local jurisdiction. By using this Software, you agree to entirely 
indemnify and hold harmless the author(s) from any criminal charges, civil 
liabilities, hardware confiscation, or legal action resulting from your use 
or misuse of the Software.
